fix: charName missing from overlay damage display + known players in Supabase + minor bugs

Changes:

- js/aria-gm.js : publishDamage() and publishHeal() now include charName in the Ably
  payload — aria-overlay.js was reading data.charName but it was always undefined,
  causing blank character name on the damage/heal overlay. All three call sites
  (applyPlayerDamage, applyPlayerHeal, applyDamageToPlayer) now pass p.name.
  collectGMData() and applyGMData() now include aria-gm-known-players-{id} in the
  Supabase sync so the GM player roster persists across devices.

- js/aria-player.js : craftPotion() had `character.vials ?? 1` — inconsistent with
  the guard above it which uses ?? 0; fixed to ?? 0. removePotion() now guards
  against character.potions being undefined before calling splice().
